<div id="review_1345232724" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1345232724" />
    <a title="Roxane" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1151637-roxane"><img alt="Roxane" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442511711p2/1151637.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1345232724?book_show_action=true">Jul 25, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Roxane" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Roxane" href="/user/show/1151637-roxane">Roxane</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1345232724" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer534050553917108610">The narrative voice is unforgettable. We get such a vivid portrait of rural Mexico through the eyes of a young girl, Ladydi, whose mother tries, as all the mothers do, to make her daughter ugly so the narcos don&apos;t take her. The chronology in the novel was hard to follow and I kept wanting more robustness from the plot. This feels more like connected vignettes. That said, this is one hell of a novel. </span>
  <span id="freeText534050553917108610" style="display:none">The narrative voice is unforgettable. We get such a vivid portrait of rural Mexico through the eyes of a young girl, Ladydi, whose mother tries, as all the mothers do, to make her daughter ugly so the narcos don't take her. The chronology in the novel was hard to follow and I kept wanting more robustness from the plot. This feels more like connected vignettes. That said, this is one hell of a novel. </span>
