  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/854918766" />
    <a title="Angela M" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4685500-angela-m"><img alt="Angela M" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1640644927p2/4685500.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/854918766?book_show_action=true">Feb 14, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Angela M" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Angela M" href="/user/show/4685500-angela-m">Angela M</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer854918766" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10395544004418857559"><br/>This is the moving story of a young girl , Ladydi , her friends and their mothers and how they cope on a daily basis with the fear that permeates the place where they live . The scenario depicted in the small mountain village of Guerrero , Mexico is so horrendous that you hope this work of fiction is purely the author&apos;s imagination . Unfortunately , it is more than likely based more on reality than we want to believe .<br/><br/>This small book is full of violence , sadness , death and fear - so much fear </span>
  <span id="freeText10395544004418857559" style="display:none"><br />This is the moving story of a young girl , Ladydi , her friends and their mothers and how they cope on a daily basis with the fear that permeates the place where they live . The scenario depicted in the small mountain village of Guerrero , Mexico is so horrendous that you hope this work of fiction is purely the author's imagination . Unfortunately , it is more than likely based more on reality than we want to believe .<br /><br />This small book is full of violence , sadness , death and fear - so much fear that these young girls dig holes to hide in so they are not stolen by the men in the drug cartels to be used as sex slaves . The fear is so great that that the mothers try to make their daughters look like sons or look so ugly that they would not be appealing .<br /><br />The writing is what I would call quiet in spite of the horrors it conveys . There are a number of excellent reviews that will give more details on the story as well as the GR description . I can only say that I was moved and saddened by this story and the plight if these girls and their mothers . I was also lifted up by the love and friendship and courage I found here .<br />Highly recommended </span>
  <a data-text-id="10395544004418857559" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


