<div id="review_851918621" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/851918621" />
    <a title="Laura" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12892069-laura"><img alt="Laura" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1449592648p2/12892069.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/851918621?book_show_action=true">Feb 11, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laura" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laura" href="/user/show/12892069-laura">Laura</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer851918621" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4898069737694529704">Guerrero, Mexico is a place where girls disguise themselves as boys to ward of rapists and kidnappers, a place where decapitated bodies hang from bridges and heroin, drug cartels and cold-blooded killers are a normal part of every day. Where vultures act as the X on an (anti)treasure map, pointing out the location of yet another dead body. A place where pesticide rains down from the sky and the place that young Ladydi calls home.<br/><br/>Prayers for the Stolen is a heart-wrenching and intimate portrayal </span>
  <span id="freeText4898069737694529704" style="display:none">Guerrero, Mexico is a place where girls disguise themselves as boys to ward of rapists and kidnappers, a place where decapitated bodies hang from bridges and heroin, drug cartels and cold-blooded killers are a normal part of every day. Where vultures act as the X on an (anti)treasure map, pointing out the location of yet another dead body. A place where pesticide rains down from the sky and the place that young Ladydi calls home.<br /><br />Prayers for the Stolen is a heart-wrenching and intimate portrayal of a girl from the jungles of Mexico. This story is incredibly powerful and helps to reveal the tragic, brutal and unfair reality that comes with being a female in Mexico. Ladydi, her mother and Maria are three females that I expect will stay in my heart and on my mind for a long time to come.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4898069737694529704" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


