<div id="review_3042793314" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3042793314" />
    <a title="Carla" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7965254-carla"><img alt="Carla" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1470265243p2/7965254.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3042793314?book_show_action=true">Nov 25, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carla" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carla" href="/user/show/7965254-carla">Carla</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3042793314" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10664223356618839597">This book left me in tears. Stunning narrative fiction that is based on life in Mexico, where Mothers hope to have &quot;ugly&quot; daughters. The hardships the poor and innocent face daily in Mexico where drug cartels, missing girls, living in fear are daily realities. Where men are either trying to get to the US to work and send money home, or are themselves leaving families to participate in crime and drugs with drug lords. How sad this book. How brilliantly written. Unforgettable. </span>
  <span id="freeText10664223356618839597" style="display:none">This book left me in tears. Stunning narrative fiction that is based on life in Mexico, where Mothers hope to have "ugly" daughters. The hardships the poor and innocent face daily in Mexico where drug cartels, missing girls, living in fear are daily realities. Where men are either trying to get to the US to work and send money home, or are themselves leaving families to participate in crime and drugs with drug lords. How sad this book. How brilliantly written. Unforgettable. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10664223356618839597" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


